.container-fluid
    a.btn.btn-primary.pull-right("(click)"="createExpression()")
        span.glyphicon.glyphicon-plus
        |  Add
    p.text-muted Named expressions can be referenced through the artifact, allowing for reuse as well a improved readability.
    br.clearfix

    #expressions("*ngIf"="knart.expressions.length > 0")
        .expression.well("*ngFor"="let e of knart.expressions")
            .btn-group.pull-right
                a.btn.btn-small.btn-danger("(click)"="deleteExpression(e)")
                    span.glyphicon.glyphicon-trash
            .clearfix
            form.form.row
                .col-sm-12.form-group
                    label(for="expression_name") Name
                    input.form-control(name="expression_name" type="text" "[(ngModel)]"="e.name" placeholder="PatientAgeInMonths")
                    p.text-muted String by which the expression can be referenced.
                .col-sm-12.form-group
                    label(for="expression_logic") ELM Logic
                    textarea.form-control(name="expression_logic" rows="10" "[(ngModel)]"="e.logic" placeholder='<elm:expression xsi:type="elm:DurationBetween" precision="Month"><elm:annotation xsi:type="a:Annotation"><a:s>Number of months from patient birth time to today</a:s></elm:annotation><elm:operand xsi:type="elm:Property" path="birthTime"><elm:source xsi:type="elm:ExpressionRef" name="Patient"/></elm:operand><elm:operand xsi:type="elm:Today" /></elm:expression>')
                    p.text-muted This must be a valid ELM expression, and may reference your bound data objects.
